        <updateDate>2019-02-25T22:18:41Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Critical Access Hospital Relief Act of </b><b>2019</b></p> <p>This bill repeals the 96-hour physician-certification requirement for inpatient critical access hospital services under Medicare. Under current law, as a condition for Medicare payment for such services, a physician must certify that a patient may reasonably be expected to be discharged or transferred to a hospital within 96 hours after admission to the critical access hospital. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
